{"title": "Mouse crawling out of passenger\u2019s meal forces Scandinavian Airlines flight to divert", "tags": "world", "timestamp": "2024-09-21", "content": "OSLO - A mouse that crawled out of a passenger\u2019s meal forced a Scandinavian Airlines (SAS) flight to make an unscheduled landing, the company said on Sept 20.\nThe incident occurred during Sept 18\u2019s Oslo to Malaga flight, forcing the plane to land in Copenhagen in Denmark.\nAirlines usually strictly prohibit rodents on board because the animals can chew through electrical wiring, key to the operation of a plane.\n\u201cBelieve it or not. A lady next to me\u2026 opened her food and a mouse jumped out,\u201d wrote one passenger, Mr Jarle Borrestad, on his Facebook page, along with a photo showing him smiling next to two other women, also smiling.\nA spokesman for SAS, Mr Oystein Schmidt, told AFP that \u201cin line with our procedures, there was a change of aircraft\u201d and the passengers were flown to Malaga on another flight.\n\u201cThis is something that happens extremely rarely,\u201d he said of the incident.\n\u201cWe have established procedures for such situations, which also include a review with our suppliers to ensure this does not happen again,\u201d he said. AFP"}